<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 30 at 5:12PM EDT until July 30 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 545 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN ANSON COUNTY...
At 512 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles east of
Marshville, or 9 miles west of Wadesboro, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Polkton, Lilesville, Peachland and White Store.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
